text: The Dr. Lawrence Branch Young House is a historic home located in Rolesville, North Carolina, a satellite town of the state capital Raleigh. Built in 1903, the Young house is the only example of Queen Anne and Colonial Revival architecture in Rolesville. The two-story white house features a wraparound porch, tall brick chimneys, and steep pyramidal roofs. In September 2003, the Dr. Lawrence Branch Young House was listed on the National Register of Historic Places. ==See also== * List of Registered Historic Places in North Carolina ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina Category:Houses completed in 1903 Category:Queen Anne architecture in North Carolina Category:Colonial Revival architecture in North Carolina Category:Houses in Wake County, North Carolina Category:National Register of Historic Places in Wake County, North Carolina
